-- THQ profit up on strong sales of "Cars"
-- 
-- Fri Feb 2, 2007 5:56am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/02/us-thq-results-idUSWEN346220070202

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Video game publisher THQ Inc. THQI.O posted better-than-expected quarterly profit on Friday due to strong sales of titles like "WWE SmackDown vs. Raw 2007," "Cars," and "SpongeBob SquarePants." 


 THQ, which is known for selling mass-market titles such as professional wrestling and Nickelodeon inspired games, said its net profit for the fiscal third quarter ended December 31 rose to $62.1 million, or 91 cents per share, from $46.9 million, or 71 cents, in the year-ago December quarter. Excluding stock option expenses, the company earned $1.00 per share, topping the average estimate of analysts polled by Reuters Estimates, which was 97 cents per share. Net sales rose to $475.7 million from $357.8 million a year ago. THQ, based in Agoura Hills, California, affirmed its fourth-quarter outlook for sales of about $146 million and net earnings of 9 cents per share, including 5 cents in stock option expenses. For the fiscal year ending in March, THQ said it expects net earnings of $1.00 per share on sales of about $1 billion. For fiscal 2008, THQ forecast net earnings of $1.11 to $1.21 per share on sales expected to range from $1.12 billion to $1.15 billion.